  "text": "Facial landmark detection gain uses the accuracy gain of landmark detection before and after attribute editing to evaluate the quality of synthesized images. For example, [CITATION_1] adopt an ERT method [CITATION_2] , which is a landmark detection algorithm trained on 300-W dataset [CITATION_3] . During testing, they divide the test sets into three components: the first containing images with the positive attribute labels, the second containing images with the negative labels, and the last containing the manipulated images from the first part. Then, the average normalized distance error is computed to evaluate the discrepancy of landmarks between the generated images and the ground truths.",
